funtions:
		A function is a block of statements ,which is used to perform a task

types of functions:
------------------
-->predefined or built in functions 
			   ex:puts(),gets(),scanf(),printf()..etc
-->user defination function:w
				ex:additionof(),subtration(),function()..etc
				

user defined function are depending upon the return and arguments these are divided into 4 types:
--->function with arguments and with return value 
return_type function_name(arguments list)
{
statements;
return interger_value;
}
example:
int add(int a,int b)
{
   return a+b;
}
--->function with arguments and with out return values
return_type function_name(arguments list)
{
statements;
printing values;
}
example:-
void add(int a,int b)
{
printf("%d",a+b);
}

--->function with out arguments and with out return values
return_type function_name(no arguments list)
{
statements;
}
example:--

void add()
{
int a,b;
scanf("%d %d",&a,&b);
printf("%d",a+b);
}

-->function with out arguments and with return values
return_type function_name()
{
statements;
return value;
}
int add()
{
int a,b;
scanf("%d %d",&a,&b);
return a+b;
}


function syntax:
----------------
return_type function_name(arguments/parameters){
	block of code
}

types of argumetns/parameters:
----------------------------
-->Actual parameters
--->formal parameters

Ex:
	//addition of two numbers by using functions
	#include<stdio.h>
	void add(int s1,int s2);
	int main(){
		int num1,num2;
		scanf("%d%d",&num1,&num2);
		add(num1,num2);
	return 0;
	}
	void add(int s1,int s2){
		int result=s1+s2;
		printf("Result =%d",result);
	}
	

